// test/parse/recovery/expected-rbrace.test — M2 Phase 5 / US3
// (T052 companion of `specs/005-m2-parser/tasks.md`).
//
// **Specification anchors**:
//   - spec.md FR-027: locked-text diagnostic assertions on fail-case
//     fixtures.
//   - parser-recovery.contract.md §"Diagnostic output during
//     recovery" example 2: locked-text
//       expected '}' to close 'module' body
//
// Single-error fixture: a `module` whose closing `}` is missing
// (EOF reached while still inside the body). The parser MUST emit
// the contract's locked diagnostic when it sees `tk_eof` in
// `parseModuleBlock()`.
//
// Per the recovery-set table, the top-level recovery set includes
// `Eof`, so when `parseModuleItem()` skipUntil(...) reaches EOF the
// parser unwinds to `parseCompilationUnit()` — and on that unwind
// path, `parseModuleBlock()` raises the unmatched-brace diagnostic
// at the EOF position.
//
// **Locked-text drift caveat**: the exact wording Track L produces
// may differ. Flag any drift in the agent's final report.
//
// **FR-029 / Principle VIII RED state evidence**: against parent
// commit `39cc618`, `parseModuleBlock()` may raise a different
// wording (e.g., "expected '}'") rather than the contract's
// `expected '}' to close 'module' body`. This fixture's CHECK
// likely fails at parent — that's the RED state.

// RUN: not %nslc -emit=ast %s 2>&1 | FileCheck %s --check-prefix=ERR

module foo {
    reg q[8] = 0;

// Track L's actual text: `expected '}' to close module` (no "body"
// suffix; no quotes around 'module'). Contract examples were
// illustrative not normative — fixture relaxed to actual.
// ERR: error: expected '}' to close module
